#: ../../source/How-To-Guides/Node-arguments.rst:30
msgid ""
"Names within a node (e.g. topics/services) can be remapped using the "
"syntax ``-r <old name>:=<new name>``. The name/namespace of the node "
"itself can be remapped using ``-r __node:=<new node name>`` and ``-r "
"__ns:=<new node namespace>``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/How-To-Guides/Node-arguments.rst:34
msgid ""
"Note that these remappings are \"static\" remappings, in that they apply "
"for the lifetime of the node. \"Dynamic\" remapping of names after nodes "
"have been started is not yet supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/How-To-Guides/Node-arguments.rst:37
msgid ""
"See `this design doc "
"<https://design.ros2.org/articles/static_remapping.html>`__ for more "
"details on remapping arguments (not all functionality is available yet)."
